 for bestpractices and # CSV Export / Reports

## Overview
Create a robust Admin CSV Export / Reports feature that enables concierge/admin users to configure and trigger CSV exports for two data domains: inquiries and payment reconciliation data. The system should provide an interactive export builder, support date-range and field selection, include filters (status, host/destination), and surface a list of recent export jobs with status updates (queued, processing, complete). The feature must be resilient to null/undefined values, guard all array operations, and follow strict runtime safety rules described in the project guidelines.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A dedicated Admin page titled CSV Export / Reports, focused on configuring and triggering CSV exports for two datasets: inquiries and payment reconciliation data.

Goals:
- Empower concierge/admin users to build custom CSV exports by selecting fields, applying filters, and choosing date ranges.
- Trigger export jobs that run on-demand or on a scheduled basis (queued/processing/complete states).
- Provide an auditable history of export jobs with timestamps, status, and downloadable CSV links.
- Ensure data extraction respects access controls (only admin/concierge users can export) and outputs sanitized, correctly-formatted CSVs.

Connected features:
- Admin CSV Export / Reports: Ability for concierge/admins to export inquiries and reconciliation data to CSV for offline processing and accounting.
- Admin Panel (V1) integrations: Inquiries list, status updates, internal notes, and export triggers feed into the same admin ecosystem.
- Security: Admin authentication and authorization must gate exports.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Export Builder section: 
  - Field picker: multi-select dropdown or checklist for available export fields (e.g., inquiry_id, guest_name, destination, host, inquiry_date, status, notes, payment_status, amount, currency, reconciliation_date, etc.).
  - Date range selectors: from and to date pickers with quick presets (Last 7 days, Last 30 days, This Month, Custom).
  - Filters: status (New, Contacted, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, etc.), host/destination filters, and optional keyword search.
  - Export button: prominent bronze-gold CTA (#A97C50) labeled “Export CSV”.
- Recent Exports panel:
  - List of export jobs with columns: Job ID, Type (Inquiries or Reconciliation), Fields, Date Range, Status (Queued/Processing/Complete/Failed), Rows Exported, Download Link (when complete), and actions (Retry, Cancel if applicable).
- Status indicators: lightweight chips or badges with color cues (e.g., queued = muted, processing = amber, complete = green, failed = red).
- Empty state and helpful tips: guidance on best practices for field selection and common export presets.
- Loading and empty states: proper skeletons or spinners with accessibility labels.

API integrations:
- No external APIs required, but frontend must integrate with internal backend APIs for:
  - Fetching export field options and supported datasets.
  - Fetching list of hosts/destinations for filters.
  - Submitting a new export job with the chosen configuration.
  - Polling or receiving real-time status updates for export jobs (via REST polling or WebSocket if available).
  - Downloading completed CSV files (securely, with expiring links or signed URLs).

---

## Components to Build
- ExportBuilderPanel
  - Props: datasetOptions, fieldOptions, initialFilters, onSubmitExport
  - State: selectedDataset, selectedFields[], dateFrom, dateTo, filters
- FieldSelector
  - Props: options[], value[], onChange
  - Behavior: multi-select with search; guard against null data
- DateRangePicker
  - Props: from, to, onRangeChange
  - Behavior: presets and manual range; validation to ensure from <= to
- FiltersPanel
  - Props: filtersConfig, currentFilters, onFiltersChange
  - Behavior: status, host, destination, keyword
- ExportButton
  - Props: disabled, onClick
  - Visual: bronze-gold CTA
- ExportsList
  - Props: exports[]
  - Behavior: render each row with status badge, metadata, and action buttons
- ExportJobModal (optional)
  - For confirming actions like Retry or Cancel; accessible
- CSVDownloadLink
  - Props: url, filename
  - Behavior: secure direct download; handles expiry gracefully
- APIClient (utility)
  - Methods: fetchFieldOptions, fetchHosts, createExportJob, fetchExports, retryExport, cancelExport
  - Guarantee: all responses are normalized to arrays with safe defaults using data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Components:
  - Build accessible, responsive React components using the project's design system.
  - Ensure visual alignment with the provided visual style (colors, typography, spacing, cards, navigation, etc.).
- State Management:
  - Use React hooks with proper defaults: useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays, useState<string> for strings, etc.
  - Maintain export form state locally and push to backend on submission.
- Data Handling:
  - Guard all array operations: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Normalize API responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Ensure default empties for optional nested objects: const { fields = [], status = 'All' } = response ?? {}.
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels for interactive elements; keyboard navigation; meaningful focus states.
- Performance:
  - Debounce search in FieldSelector if needed; lazy-load host/destination options if datasets are large.
- Validation:
  - Validate date range before submission; ensure at least one field is selected; ensure user has export permissions.
- Security:
  - Ensure all API calls include authentication state checks on the backend; frontend should surface 403/401 appropriately.

### Backend
- API Endpoints (to implement or adapt):
  - GET /admin/export/fields?dataset={inquiries|reconciliation} -> returns available fields for that dataset.
  - GET /admin/export/hosts -> returns list of hosts/destinations for filtering.
  - POST /admin/export -> creates an export job with payload:
    - dataset: "inquiries" | "reconciliation"
    - fields: string[]
    - dateFrom: string (ISO)
    - dateTo: string (ISO)
    - filters: { status?: string, hostId?: string, destinationId?: string, search?: string }
    - userId: requester (for auditing)
  - GET /admin/export/{exportId} -> job status and metadata
  - GET /admin/export/{exportId}/download -> secure signed URL for CSV if status === "complete"
  - POST /admin/export/{exportId}/retry -> retry failed export
  - POST /admin/export/{exportId}/cancel -> cancel a queued or in-process export
- Data Models:
  - ExportJob: { id, dataset, fields, dateFrom, dateTo, filters, status, rows, createdAt, updatedAt, userId, errorMessage, downloadUrl }
  - Inquiry, PaymentReconciliation: existing schemas; ensure projection to only requested fields in export job generation.
- Processing Logic:
  - Validate input strictly: ensure dataset is allowed, fields exist for dataset, dates valid, user authorized.
  - Safety: handle null data gracefully; export jobs should never crash due to missing related records.
  - Implement export generation as background task (queue) to avoid request-time heavy processing.
  - On success, generate CSV with header row matching selected fields; ensure proper escaping of commas, quotes, newlines.
- Security:
  - Role-based access: only Admin/Concierge can access/export; enforce in backend.
  - Data access controls: ensure only permitted fields are included per role.
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation of all inputs; normalize payload; guard against SQL/NoSQL injection.

### Integration
- Data Flow:
  - Frontend fetches available fields/hosts for builder, submits export config to backend.
  - Backend validates, enqueues export job, returns jobId.
  - Frontend polls or subscribes to job status; upon completion, frontend shows download link.
  - Admin can Retry or Cancel via dedicated endpoints.
- State Synchronization:
  - Use a shared API client with standardized response handling; consistently apply nullish coalescing and array guards.
- Error Handling:
  - UI-friendly error messages; handle 401/403; show actionable guidance.

---

## User Experience Flow
1. Admin logs into the Roam Resort Admin Panel.
2. Navigates to CSV Export / Reports page.
3. Views Export Builder:
   - Chooses dataset: Inquiries or Payment Reconciliation.
   - Picks desired fields from available field list.
   - Sets date range with presets or custom dates.
   - Applies filters: status, host, destination, keyword search.
   - Clicks Export CSV (bronze-gold CTA).
4. System validates input and creates an export job (status: queued).
5. Export job appears in Recent Exports with status, metadata, and a pending download (not yet available).
6. Job status transitions to Processing, then Complete.
7. On Complete, a download link becomes active; admin can click to download the CSV.
8. If a job fails, admin can Retry or Cancel; logs show errorMessage.
9. Admin can filter/search the Exports list and sort by date or status.
10. Optional: Admin receives in-app notification when export completes.

---

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - ExportJob: { id: string, dataset: "inquiries" | "reconciliation", fields: string[], dateFrom: string, dateTo: string, filters: object, status: "queued" | "processing" | "complete" | "failed" | "cancelled", rows?: number, createdAt: string, updatedAt: string, userId: string, errorMessage?: string, downloadUrl?: string }
  - Inquiry: existing schema; PaymentReconciliation: existing schema; ensure export projection matches fields[]
- API Endpoints:
  - GET /admin/export/fields?dataset={inquiries|reconciliation}
  - GET /admin/export/hosts
  - POST /admin/export
  - GET /admin/export/{exportId}
  - GET /admin/export/{exportId}/download
  - POST /admin/export/{exportId}/retry
  - POST /admin/export/{exportId}/cancel
- Security:
  - OAuth/JWT-based authentication for admin/concierge roles.
  - Authorization checks on every endpoint; 403 if unauthorized.
- Validation:
  - Validate dataset, fields against allowed list per dataset.
  - DateFrom/DateTo must be valid ISO dates; dateFrom <= dateTo.
  - Filters values must be whitelisted (e.g., statuses, host IDs).
  - Guard against null/undefined inputs; defaults provided by backend.

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Admins can configure and trigger exports for inquiries and reconciliation data via a clear Export Builder UI.
- [ ] The system validates inputs (dataset, fields, date range, filters) and returns meaningful errors for invalid configurations.
- [ ] Exports are processed in the background; a new export job appears in the Exports list with status transitions: queued -> processing -> complete.
- [ ] On completion, a secure download link is provided and downloadable CSV contains exactly the selected fields in the specified order, with proper CSV escaping.
- [ ] All array operations and data accesses guard against null/undefined; use data ?? [] and Array.isArray() where appropriate.
- [ ] Responses and state management follow the runtime safety rules (initial states, nullish coalescing, optional chaining, and destructuring with defaults).
- [ ] Security: only admin/concierge roles can access; unauthorized access results in 403/401 with actionable messaging.

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system to deliver a modern luxury editorial experience.

- Card Design:
  - Soft rounded corners (8–12px), subtle elevations, light borders.
  - Hover states with slight lift and bronze accent.
- Navigation:
  - Top navigation with transparent behavior over hero sections; solid on scroll.
  - Minimalist links, ample spacing; mobile collapses to a clean hamburger menu.
- Data Visualization:
  - If charts appear (e.g., export trends), use minimal, elegant visuals with bronze-gold accents and navy axes.
- Interactive Elements:
  - Bronze-gold CTAs (#A97C50); primary buttons on light/dark backgrounds.
  - Focus states with accent color; accessible button states and keyboard navigation.
- Typography:
  - Headlines: Playfair Display (or similar).
